`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
- The key architectural insight here is the **two-layer seed system**: `hedgePlacement.ts` uses integer seeds (via `createRNG`), while the world layer uses string seeds (via `scopedRNG`). Bridging them with `hashString("maze-{worldSeed}-{x}-{z}")` creates a deterministic per-chunk integer seed without coupling the two layers.
- The existing `hedgePlacement.ts` was already doing the heavy lifting (recursive backtracker, GLB path construction, decoration logic). `mazeGenerator.ts` is a pure adapter that handles coordinate transformation and ECS type wrapping.
